author: Nate Mink | nmink@syracuse.com
title: Syracuse football-Louisville kickoff time and TV information announced
text:
Syracuse, N.Y. â€” The Syracuse-Louisville football game on Nov. 7 will kick off at 12:30 p.m. at Papa John's Cardinal Stadium in Louisville, it was announced Monday. 
The game will be televised regionally on the ACC network. 
It will be Syracuse's first trip to Louisville since 2011, when 44,817 watched the Cardinals defeat the Orange, 27-10, the first of five straight losses to close the season and deny bowl eligibility after a 5-2 start. 
This year, Syracuse is mired in a four-game losing streak heading into Saturday's matchup at No. 17 Florida State, which is coming off a spectacular loss at Georgia Tech that saw the Jackets return a blocked field goal for the winning touchdown as time expired. 
It was the Seminoles' first conference loss since 2012. 
Louisville travels to Wake Forest on Friday night. The Cardinals will be looking to move to .500 after an 0-3 start, in which all three games were decided by one score. Louisville lost, 41-21 at Florida State two weeks ago.
